---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Our Story | Brooklynite Designs">
  <section class="container-shell grid gap-10 py-16 md:grid-cols-[0.85fr_1.15fr]">
    <div>
      <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-brick">Our story</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 font-display text-5xl font-semibold">A family-run Brooklyn shop</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="grid gap-5 text-lg leading-8 text-ink/72">
      <p>Brooklynite Designs celebrates the borough through soft apparel, baby gifts, hats, knits, art, and accessories that feel personal instead of mass-market.</p>
      <p>Products are organized around how people actually shop: new baby gifts, useful apparel, local pride, small keepsakes, and easy bundles.</p>
      <p>The rebuild keeps that warmth while making the site faster, more searchable, and ready for Stripe Checkout, Firestore inventory, and lightweight family admin tools.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
